    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "This issue was reported in a software I contribute to (https://savannah.gnu.org/bugs/index.php?48343) that uses an embedded python interpreter.\r\nThe non-existant directory thing is a bit contrived and may not be how the user got there, but that was the simplest way to reproduce the problem.\r\n\r\nThe issue is not that the message is not clear, it is that if the exception is not caught the user is ejected out of the python interpreter. As far as I'm concerned, silently setting self.starting_dir to None when the getcwd() fails looks fine."
