    "created_at": "2017-11-27T10:55:54Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-11-27T10:55:54Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "When I launch `ipython` in a directory that doesn't exist, there's a clear error message:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[TerminalIPythonApp] ERROR | Current working directory doesn't exist.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere's no obviously correct behaviour here, and I think the current behaviour is reasonable. I guess creating the embedded shell could throw an error with a more explanatory message. But if you want some nicer behaviour, I think it's up to your application to check for the cwd and change directory if necessary."
